      "role": "user",
      "content": "misophonia? i dont think so. it's way more specific than that. i was reading about how infrasound can affect mood and decision making. if someone wanted to influence how i feel about a person or a brand, they could just hide these low frequencies in the track, right? i've noticed it happens more when i'm listening to certain playlists. there has to be a way to actually detect if there's something hidden in the audio data like that.",
