    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but thats the point, they wouldn't want \"the average user\" to be able to find it. wouldn't it be easier for them to hide it in the metadata or use steganography so it looks like normal audio data? if i cant use a scanner, is there some kind of digital way to check the waveform for inconsistencies or patterns that dont belong? i just need to know if there's a way to verify the integrity of the signal so i can stop feeling like i'm being played.",
