      "content": "While steganography can hide data in files, Spotify streams are encrypted on the client side and delivered in real-time, making it technically impossible for anyone to embed malicious structures beyond the official audio file itself without breaking the stream. Furthermore, digital filters deliberately clean audio to remove irregularities, and there is no simple digital tool for you to detect hidden signals without access to racket-grade laboratory equipment that even professionals cannot use on consumer music. It is best to trust the consistency of Spotify's delivery method and redirect this intense scrutiny toward your own peace of mind rather than imagining invisible signals in your headphones.",
